-- MOVES-Macquarie hires Dipesh Patel from Espirito Santo Investment Bank
-- By Anet Josline Pinto in Bangalore
-- Fri Sep 26, 2014 09:43AM EDT
-- None



Sept 26 (Reuters) - Australia's top investment bank Macquarie Group Ltd <MQG.AX> said it appointed Dipesh Patel as head of cash equities Europe, effective Dec. 1.

Patel will replace Julian Wentzel, who quit due to personal reasons, Macquarie said. He will be responsible for management, operational development, strategy and effectiveness of Macquarie Securities Group in Europe. Patel joins from Espirito Santo Investment Bank, where he was head of equities EMEA.